<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,152,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,413,439]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[881,952,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">flavus</emphasis>
– yellow, 
<emphasis box="[1079,1158,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">nervus</emphasis>
– vein, referring to the wing pattern.
</paragraph>
